                            <div class="slide slide1">
                                <h1>Mark Brooks</h1>
                                <img src="img/mark-brooks.png" alt="Mark Brooks" width="287" height="385">
                                <h2>Bio</h2>
                                <div>Mark is one of the world’s most experienced executive coaches and team facilitators. Working primarily at board level, he specialises in creating an environment where people can express themselves freely before making powerful choices and lasting changes. Recent projects include 18 months coaching the CEO of a FTSE 100 company and two years working with the COO of a global finance organisation’s Asia Division.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    As well as his work with senior executives, Mark has run numerous international corporate change programmes across a wide range of sectors, from finance and pharmaceutical, to manufacturing and food.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Past and present clients include Schroders Plc, Fidelity International, Lloyds Bank Treasury Division, GlaxoSmithKline, OSI Foods, The Timken Company, Transocean and Guys &amp; St. Thomas NHS Foundation Trust.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Mark lives in the UK.</div>
                                <h2>Professionnal Qualifications</h2>
                                <div><ul>
                                        <li>
                                            Neuro-Linguistic Programming (NLP) at The University of California (Dr John Grinder)</li>
                                        <li>
                                            Postgraduate diploma in Change Agent Skills and Strategies with the Human Potential Research Group at Surrey University (Dr Paul Barber)</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="slide slide1">
                                <h1>Diedre Dennis</h1>
                                <img src="img/deirdre-dennis.png" alt="Diedre Dennis" width="287" height="385">
                                <h2>Bio</h2>
                                <div>Formerly a respected college professor of English, Humanities and Psychology, Diedre combines her knowledge of learning and human nature with a lifelong study and training of horses. The result is a unique approach to facilitation that focuses on the animal’s remarkable power to reveal our deepest thoughts, talents and feelings. When applied to the corporate world, this rare combination of equine insight and in-depth knowledge of psychological processes can, among other things, help leaders to flourish; create stronger and more productive teams, and prepare everyone from CEOs to senior executives for cultural change.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Diedre is currently working on her PhD.</div>
                                <h2>Professionnal Qualifications</h2>
                                <div><ul>
                                        <li>
                                            CHA (Certified Horsemanship Association)</li>
                                        <li>
                                            EAGALA (Equine Assisted Growth and Learning Association)</li>
                                        <li>
                                            PATH (Professional Association of Therapeutic Horsemanship)</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="slide slide1">
                                <h1>Juliet Fraser-Ellis</h1>
                                <img src="img/juliet-fraser-ellis.png" alt="Juliet Fraser-Ellis" width="287" height="385">
                                <h2>Bio</h2>
                                <div>Juliet specialises in supporting management teams to develop and implement their vision and values. In a career spanning 30 years, she has helped individuals, teams and organisations in Europe and the US, across all business sectors change their behaviour to improve commercial success.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Alongside her work in this field, Juliet co-founded a management consultancy specialising in customer relationship management and, as Managing Director, grew the business to a multi-million pound turnover within a few years.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Companies that have called on Juliet’s skills include Coca Cola, Nationwide, IBM, British Telecom, Pilkington, MSAS Global Logistics, BUPA, Next, British Midland Airways, HSBC, First Direct and Getty Images.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Juliet lives in the UK.</div>
                                <h2>Professionnal Qualifications</h2>
                                <div><ul>
