                            <div class="slide slide1">
                                <h1>Simon D'Arcy</h1>
                                <img src="img/simon_darcy.png" alt="Simon D&#39;Arcy" width="287" height="385">
                                <h2>Bio</h2>
                                <div>Simon specialises in guiding senior executives through the real life challenges they face using an approach that embraces facilitation, coaching and sound assessment. Recently, he has applied his expertise to a number of large-scale projects, including the development and implementation of a culture change programme for a 2000-person global energy company.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Before working with Phoenix Obsidian, Simon was a senior consultant at Milandro Communications Inc, where he first discovered his passion for creating long-term change in organisations based on the core values of authenticity, accountability, community and constant learning. He has worked with over 850 groups of managers and leaders from over 300 companies on 6 continents.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    Simon’s recent clients include ConocoPhillips, Merrill Lynch Canada, Sun MicroSystems, United States Gypsum Corporation, RVI Group, DCP Midstream, Gold’s Gym and Network Equipment Technologies.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    He lives in Santa Barbara, California</div>
                                <h2>Professionnal Qualifications</h2>
